{"block1":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">What knowledge do you have when it comes to nutrition? Do you plan out your diet? If you have one, are you interested in improving it? Are you sure you are receiving what you need? If you don&#39;t have the answers to these questions, read these tips.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"\/images\/portrait-of-whole-wheat-flour.jpg\" class=\"img_left \" alt=\"portrait of whole wheat flour\" style=\"float: left; padding: 8px; padding-left: 0;\" \/>&nbsp;Use an online meal diary to track your meals. If you see that you&#39;ve gained weight, evaluate what you&#39;ve been eating. Some foods are more calorie dense than others, so&nbsp;you don&#39;t have to be eating a large amount of food to pack in the pounds. If you document and track what you eat at every meal, you can get a better overall picture of your dietary intake and make adjustments from that. The manner in which meals are prepared at home can greatly affect the nutritional outcome of foods. Steaming or boiling foods will cook them without adding any extra fat. Food preparation is an important element of <a href=\"http:\/\/www.mensfitness.com\/nutrition\/what-to-eat\/back-to-basics-creating-a-healthy-diet-plan\"  >creating a healthy diet<\/a>. When baking, use whole wheat flour rather than white to up the nutrition value. Whole wheat flour is full of fiber and nutrients, while white flour is full of empty calories.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When you are making your child a healthy meal, substitute a baked potato for french fries. Cut a potato into halves and use cherry tomatoes, low fat cheese or yogurt to decorate it.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Record your progress in a daily journal or notebook. If your <a href=\"http:\/\/www.nhlbi.nih.gov\/health\/health-topics\/topics\/hbp\"  >blood pressure is high<\/a>, track it with a daily log. Similarly, if you are working on shedding excess pounds, write about the process of changing your dietary habits and how much weight you&#39;ve&nbsp;dropped along the way.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Do you have the knowledge you need about nutrition? Have these tips left you better equipped to find a nutrition plan that works? Can you properly modify a nutritional plan to fit your needs? And are you fully receiving everything your body needs with your nutrition plan?&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n"}